  "text": "For the BMWP-based indices, bias associated with misclassification of Chironomidae and Oligochaeta increased as the modal value increased and was consistently greater for mildly transformed and non-transformed data (Fig 8a) . The net effect of all misclassified taxa (according to [CITATION_1] ) was most pronounced for raw abundance data where it accounted for a positive bias of 1.3 units (Fig 8b) . In general the risk of bias decreased with increasing index scores and became negative for transformed data between index values 6 to 9 (Fig 8b) .",
